methods:

java methods are used To reuse code: define the code once, and use it many times.

for creating method it must be declared within the class.

 types of methods:
1. default method
2. parameterized method

in default method:
there is no need to give parameter list.

in parameterized method:
one can give parameter list and return the value if needed.



for example: (default method example)

public class Main{
    
    public void method1(){                                  //method initialization
            System.out.println("I am method 1");            //method body
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args){                 
        Main m1 = new Main();                               //Object creation
        m1.method1();                                       //method calling
    }  
}



for example: (Parameterized method example)

public class Main{
    
    static void myMethod( String myName){
        
        System.out.println("hii this is "+myName);
    }
    
    public static void main (String[] args){
        myMethod("Raju");
        myMethod("sheetal");
        myMethod("Vasu");
    }
    
}







